@dragonman225 

> Mark ProseMirror's root [contenteditable](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Global_attributes/contenteditable) element with aria-live="off"

Oh right, this is a smart solution, as markOthers only checks for `[aria-live]` with no value. 

I can confirm this works with VoiceOver, but not sure about other SRs.

```html
  <button id="update">Update status text</button>

  <div aria-live="off">
    <div id="status" aria-live="polite" role="status">Ready</div>
  </div>

  <script>
    let n = 0;
    document.getElementById("update").addEventListener("click", () => {
      n++;
      document.getElementById("status").textContent = `Update ${n}`;
    });
  </script>
```

But keep in mind that `aria-hidden="true"` still needs to be applied to the ProseMirror container while the dialog is open for to actually be "modal", so the `readonly` solution might be better still.
